<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="307" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1660,1865]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1768,1793]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Remarks.</emphasis>
Sigwart 
<emphasis box="[428,491,1768,1793]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">et al.</emphasis>
(2011) demonstrated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" box="[810,944,1768,1793]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[810,944,1768,1793]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Leptochiton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not monophyletic based on molecular analyses of three genes; accordingly 
<taxonomicName authority="Sirenko, 2018" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2018" box="[571,705,1804,1829]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" sensu="stricto" status="s.s.">
<emphasis box="[571,705,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Leptochiton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[713,749,1805,1828]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[713,741,1805,1828]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">s.s</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is restricted to the North Atlantic and Mediterranean. I here use 
<taxonomicName authority="Sirenko, 2018" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2018" box="[195,329,1840,1865]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" sensu="lato" status="s.l.">
<emphasis box="[195,329,1840,1865]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Leptochiton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[336,369,1840,1865]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[336,362,1840,1865]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">s.l</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
according to the traditional morphological concept.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
